## 🔐 4. Security Architecture

### Layer 1: API Token (WordPress ↔ Next.js)
- 48-char random hex token signup par generate hota hai
- WordPress plugin Settings mein paste karna hota hai
- `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header se Next.js verify karta hai

### Layer 2: JWT Session (User ↔ Next.js)
- `auth_token` HTTP-Only cookie (JavaScript se readable nahi)
- Payload: `{ userId, username, iat, exp }`
- Remember me: 30 din | Normal: 24 ghante

### Layer 3: HMAC-SHA256 Token (Next.js → Cloudflare Worker)
```
Signature Input:  "uuid:expires:action:SECRET_SALT"
Algorithm:        SHA-256
Output:           64-char hex signature

Security guarantee:
  - Koi token ke `source` URL ko change kare → Signature mismatch → 401
  - Bina SECRET_SALT ke valid signature impossible
  - Token 1 hour baad expire → Captured tokens useless
```

### Layer 4: `e.isTrusted` Bot Prevention
```javascript
element.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
  if (!e.isTrusted) return; // Programmatic clicks = false → REJECT
  // Real human mouse click = true → Proceed
});
// Bots element.click() se token nahi nikaal paate!
```

### Layer 5: Token Expiry
- Har token exactly 1 ghante ke baad expire
- Dobara play karne ke liye naya token automatically generate hota hai

