## 📊 8. Full Visitor Journey (Step-by-Step)

```
Step 1 — Page Load
   User Facebook ad click karta hai
   WordPress post load
   PHP: Bot? (User-Agent) → Bot hai → Only article text, no video
   PHP: Social traffic? (fbclid param) → Yes → Inject player JS

Step 2 — Ghost Thumbnail
   JS: fetch('/api/media?action=get_thumb&uuid=a1b2c3d4')
   Next.js: Redis check → MySQL → return thumbnail URL
   Screen: Image + play button overlay (actual video element nahi!)

Step 3 — Play Click
   User clicks play → e.isTrusted = true (real click)
   Show: "Loading secure stream..."

Step 4 — Token Request
   JS: fetch('/api/media?action=get_stream&uuid=a1b2c3d4')
   Next.js:
     1. Redis/MySQL se video info
     2. expires = now + 3600
     3. HMAC sha256("uuid:expires:stream:SALT") = signature
     4. payload = { uuid, action, source(HIDDEN), filename, expires, signature }
     5. token = base64(JSON.stringify(payload))
     6. Return: player_html with <video src="worker?token=XYZ">

Step 5 — Player Inject
   JS: container.innerHTML = player_html
   Browser: Starts video request to Cloudflare Worker

Step 6 — Edge Streaming
   Browser → Worker: GET /fast_stream?token=XYZ
                     Range: bytes=0-
   Worker:
     1. base64 decode token
     2. expires check → valid
     3. sha256 reverify → signature match
     4. fetch(source, { Range: "bytes=0-" })
     5. pipe body → user (zero-copy, no RAM buffer)
   Browser: HTTP 206 Partial → Video plays!

Step 7 — Seeking
   User skips to 2 min mark
   Browser: Range: bytes=60000000-
   Worker: Same valid token → forward range → 206 response
   User: Instantly jumps to that point, no rebuffering!
```

